SIMPLE: three-piled
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Three-piled
<hw>Three"-piled`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having the quality of three-pile; best; most costly.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou art good velvet; thou 'rt <qex>three-piled</qex> piece.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: Extravagant; exaggerated; high-flown.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Three-piled</xex> hyperboles.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Accustomed to wearing three-pile; hence, of high
rank, or wealth.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Three-piled</xex>
people.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Three-ply</ent>⟦br⟧
